From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0070/N] globalDefinitions: clamp LogKlassAlignment >= 0 under CHERI

`LogKlassAlignment = LogKlassAlignmentInBytes - LogHeapWordSize` was 3-3=0
on standard LP64, but becomes 3-4 = **-1** under our CHERI build (where
patch 0060 sets LogHeapWordSize=4). Negative log value, cast through
unsigned in downstream shift computations, produces:

  64 - LogKlassAlignment = 64 - (-1) = 65
  (65 & 63) = 1                                    (immr fine)
  but anywhere using `LogKlassAlignment` raw as shift produces huge
  values when cast to unsigned

Semantic: LogKlassAlignment represents "Klass alignment in HeapWord
units, log2". Klass-aligned to 8 bytes; HeapWord = 16 on CHERI. Ratio
8/16 = 0.5 < 1, log is negative.

Empirically the JVM aarch64 codegen produces a shift=64 inside an
`op_shifted_reg(0xa, LSL, ...)` call during boot (the `0xa` decode is
the logical-shifted-register family: andr/orr/eor). This trips the
6-bit imms-field encoder guarantee at assembler_aarch64.hpp:248.

Fix: clamp LogKlassAlignment to 0 under purecap. This may produce
inefficient klass-pointer encoding (no benefit from alignment-derived
extra range), but we have UseCompressedClassPointers OFF anyway, so
the compressed-klass path isn't exercised.

Empirical: build clean, JVM still crashes at the SAME location after
146 bootclasses. So this isn't the actual shift=64 source — committed
because the clamp is correctness-good independent of the immediate
crash (avoids a negative-log constant that may haunt other code paths).

Next investigation: cap-aware stack walk to capture more than one frame
above the op_shifted_reg call site. __builtin_return_address(N>0) is
unreliable on CHERI; need explicit FP-chain walk via inline-asm
`mov %0, c29`.

Refs: docs/12_simd_codegen_wordsize_seam.md

diff --git a/src/hotspot/share/utilities/globalDefinitions.hpp b/src/hotspot/share/utilities/globalDefinitions.hpp
--- a/src/hotspot/share/utilities/globalDefinitions.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/utilities/globalDefinitions.hpp
@@ -557,7 +557,17 @@ extern int LogMinObjAlignment;
 extern int LogMinObjAlignmentInBytes;

 const int LogKlassAlignmentInBytes = 3;
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+// CHERI purecap: LogHeapWordSize=4 > LogKlassAlignmentInBytes=3, which would make
+// LogKlassAlignment = -1 (underflow). The semantic "Klass alignment in HeapWord
+// units" is < 1 on CHERI (Klass aligned to 8 bytes, HeapWord = 16). Clamp to 0:
+// downstream shifts using LogKlassAlignment as the bit count would otherwise
+// produce shift=64 (=BitsPerWord - LogKlassAlignment = 64-(-1) = 65, &63 = 1, or
+// similar overflows) and trip the aarch64 op_shifted_reg encoder.
+const int LogKlassAlignment        = 0;
+#else
 const int LogKlassAlignment        = LogKlassAlignmentInBytes - LogHeapWordSize;
+#endif
 const int KlassAlignmentInBytes    = 1 << LogKlassAlignmentInBytes;
 const int KlassAlignment           = KlassAlignmentInBytes / HeapWordSize;

